result.formatted_address: The Octagon, 6 Sha Tsui Rd, Tsuen Wan, Hong Kong
result.name: Sportful Garden Restaurant

reviews.text: If you want some decent dim sum. This is joint will suffice. The prawn dumplings are delicious, with a thin pastry. Intact most of their other dumplings are good too.
Fast service, really good food. Excellent choice if you are in there.
Food not that bad, but the overall of the decoration and foods looks quite awful. Though the manager is a nice guy~

A typical Chinese restaurant that serves dim sum during the day. I've only been here for lunch. Reliable. Presentable. I don't remember being adversely affected by their msg so that's a plus. Nothing bad to add, that's also a plus.

The food itself lives up to Sportful Garden's reputation.

A big however, this shop is in need of a competent management... 

Management issue #1:   the long queue for table is totally avoidable. There were plenty of empty table which was left without tidying up.  The number of table is sufficient to accommodate the whole queue. If there isn't any ulterior motive for leaving those table for some vip, this is a pure failure of coordination.

Management issue #2:  the staff member can rebuff customers enquiries freely and openly.  This is either an inadequate staff training... Or a dereliction of duty by the management on quality of service reassurance.

I am raising this in length because I don't want to see a restaurant offering good food being ruined by its unwelcoming staff...

result.name: 陶源酒家

reviews.text: 地方大,坐得舒服,早茶價錢可接受,但午飯及晚飯時段,比一般酒樓貴一點,而地點比較遠,不近地鐵及西鐵.
款式少，偏貴，地點唔就腳所以易揾位
早茶優恵非常抵，2元8角一盅盅頭更是必叫之選。點心味道一流，服務態度好。

出品水準高，
座住舒適 。

服务員親切，
管理人員欠笑容，
可能壓力太大！
點心款式製作不失傳統風味，卻充滿創意！
